4 Partitions

Number of Fats...
Number of entries per FAT
Each entry is 32-bits - 4 bytes

sum is number of clusters

Total sectors per partition - 4 bytes (2^32)
Bytes per sector - 2 byte
Number of sectors per FAT - 4 bytes


(4 Partitions per file system)(2^32 sectors per FAT) * (2^16 bytes per sector) / (4 bytes per entry (cluster) = 2^48 clusters per FAT...
but...

Cluster ID 0xFFFFFEF - 0x2 = 0xFFFFFED
